  "recommendation": "Prescribe lovastatin at the standard recommended starting dose per disease-specific guidelines. No dose adjustment is required for the SLCO1B1 Increased Function phenotype. If clinically indicated, dose titration should follow standard lipid-lowering protocols. This genotype is not associated with elevated myopathy risk, so standard monitoring is appropriate.",
  "classification": "No Recommendation",
  "implication": "SLCO1B1 Increased Function (associated with alleles such as *1b and *14, e.g., c.388A>G and/or c.463C>A variants) results in enhanced OATP1B1-mediated hepatic uptake of lovastatin, leading to lower systemic plasma drug concentrations and reduced peripheral muscle exposure. This phenotype is not associated with increased risk of statin-induced myopathy; evidence from fluvastatin studies (PMID 18781850) suggests that increased-function alleles (*14) may actually enhance LDL-C lowering efficacy. However, specific pharmacokinetic data for lovastatin in SLCO1B1 Increased Function carriers are limited, and no formal dose adjustment recommendation exists beyond standard clinical practice."
}
